# Next.js Frontends

## Apps

| App | Path | Port |
|-----|------|------|
| Board | `apps/board` | 3000 |
| Intel | `apps/intel` | 3001 |

Both talk to NestJS API at `API_URL` (default `http://localhost:4000`). Run on host via `pnpm dev:board` / `pnpm dev:intel`.

## Auth (backend-owned)

Frontends do **not** run their own OIDC. To log in, redirect the user to the API: `GET {API_URL}/auth/login`. The API runs the MSAL flow (callback `http://localhost:4000/auth/callback`) and returns an app session JWT. Store it and send as `Authorization: Bearer` on API calls. No NextAuth, no MSAL in the frontend.

Auth gate screens (`AuthScreen`) must always offer **Sign out** (`GET /auth/logout` — federated Entra logout) and **Sign in as a different user** (`/auth/login?prompt=select_account`) whenever a token exists. Clearing `localStorage` alone is not enough — Microsoft SSO keeps the browser session.

## Board UI requirements

- Entra SSO login gate
- Kanban columns: todo, in_progress, review, done
- Task cards: health score badge — green >70, amber 40–70, red <40
- Mood picker on status change, comment, reassignment modals
- Roles: `pulse-admin` and `pulse-member` only (block `pulse-viewer`)

## Intel UI requirements

- All roles including `pulse-viewer` (read-only)
- Live activity feed via SSE (no polling)
- Health leaderboard: tasks sorted by `health_score` ASC
- Momentum meter: rolling average mood over last 24h
- AI panel: persistent per-user chat (`intel_chat_turns`) — `GET /intel/chat` hydrates on load, `POST /intel/query` streams RAG answers and saves turns, prior turns included in LLM context; `DELETE /intel/chat` clears history; scrollable chat UI with source citations; input clears after send

## Conventions

- App Router, TypeScript strict, **Tailwind CSS v4** (`@import "tailwindcss"`, `@theme` in `globals.css`, `@tailwindcss/postcss`)
- `'use client'` only when hooks or browser APIs required
- API calls server-side where possible; SSE client-side in Intel feed
- Import shared types from `@pulse/shared-types`
